Ingredients.2: 3 medium russet potatoes, or more to taste, sliced into even strips

Ingredients.7: 1 teaspoon salt, or more to taste

Directions.1: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.

Directions.2: Pour olive oil into a large resealable plastic bag and add potatoes. Seal the bag and shake to coat every piece with oil.

Directions.3: Combine Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, salt, and pepper in a second resealable bag. Pour oiled potatoes into the bag, seal, and toss well to coat.

Directions.4: Spread potatoes on the prepared baking sheet.

Directions.5: Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes. Flip potatoes over and bake until crisp on the outside and soft on the inside, about 15 minutes more.
